The paper deals with the problem of object classification, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves generative probabilistic modeling, which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The model also involves encoding semantic relationships, which is a common theme in natural language processing (cs.CL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the experiments involve benchmark datasets, which are commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
